From b6682989be1d6f5595c894a846c8ce654a63bf24 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 09:45:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 29/39] WIP: media: tuners: r848: make file-local functions
 static

A large number of internal helper functions (R848_Freq_Sel, I2C_Write,
R848_PLL, R848_MUX, R848_IMR, R848_SetStandard, R848_SetFrequency and
friends) are only used within r848.c and are not declared in any header.
Mark them static to fix the many -Wmissing-prototypes warnings.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/media/tuners/r848.c | 48 ++++++++++++++++++-------------------
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+), 24 deletions(-)

